sentences: Primo Casale (1904–1981) was an Italian-born Venezuelan conductor, composer, and violinist.
He came to Venezuela in 1948 and became one of the foremost teachers of composition in the country at the Conservatorio Nacional de Música Juan José Landaeta.
In 1949 he founded the choir of the Caracas opera.
This group, which played for several years without any financial support, made its debut with Elisir d' Amore on May 29, 1950.
